Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with computing the distortion power at the receiver side of an FBMC/OQAM-based OFDMA uplink channel, which involves analyzing the information transmission and reception process. 
2. cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing the distortion in a multiple access channel, which is a key aspect of communication networks. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with analyzing the performance of a multiple access channel, which is a fundamental aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper involves analyzing the distortion in a signal processing system, which is a key aspect of the field of signal processing. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with analyzing the distortion in a multimedia communication system, which involves the transmission and reception of multiple types of media.
